Your rights as our customer
In accordance with European and national legal provisions on the protection of personal data of individuals, you have the following rights:
● To request the deletion of your personal data or the restriction of their processing. We reserve the right to refuse such request where their storage is necessary for the fulfillment of a legal obligation or for the defense of a legitimate right in a judicial proceedings.
● To request from us free of charge information regarding the storage and processing of your personal data.
● To have access to your personal data we collect and store. At your express request we will confirm if we process your data and we will provide you with a copy of said data.
● To oppose at any time the collection and processing of your data.
● To request corrections or completions of your personal data.
● To request the transfer of your personal data to another operator, this will only be done under your personal request.
● To request that your data not be the subject of a decision based exclusively on the automatic processing of said data.
● To contact ANSPDCP - National Authority for the Supervision of Personal Data Processing (based at 28-30 Gheorghe Magheru Blvd., Sector 1, Bucharest, E-mail: anspdcp@dataprotection.ro, Tel : +40.318.059.211)
Your data is safe with us and we assure you that we are constantly taking all measures to comply with the legal provisions in this matter.
We encourage you to contact us whenever you want more information regarding the collection and processing of your personal data or when you find any violation of your rights by writing an email to support@extasy.com, without to limit in any way your right to address the competent authorities.
